EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to animals; revising provisions governing the
seizure of animals under certain circumstances; revising
provisions governing acts constituting torture or cruelty to
animals; revising certain penalties and remedies for acts
of animal cruelty; authorizing a court to issue a temporary
restraining order against a person who commits certain
acts of animal cruelty; revising certain provisions
governing the ownership and care of animals treated
cruelly; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, “torture” of or “cruelty” to an animal includes every act,
2 omission or neglect, whereby unjustifiable physical pain, suffering or death is
3 caused or permitted. (NRS 574.050) Section 2 of this bill separates the definition of
4 “torture” of and “cruelty” to animals to provide that: (1) “cruelty” includes every
5 act, omission or neglect, whereby unjustifiable physical pain, suffering or death of
6 an animal is caused or permitted; and (2) “torture” means every act taken to inflict
7 on or prolong pain, suffering or death to an animal.
8 Section 1.6 of this bill authorizes a court to issue a temporary restraining order
9 against a person charged with committing certain unlawful acts of animal cruelty.
10 Existing law requires certain officers to: (1) take possession of an animal which
11 is being treated cruelly; and (2) give to the owner a notice containing certain
